The paper deals with the design of polynomial-time approximation schemes (PTAS) for Max-2-CSPs, which are a type of optimization problem in computer science. The paper also discusses the notion of treewidth-pliability, which is a concept from graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
